metadata.description: Comprehensive 500kV, 345kV, and 230kV transmission lines in the Western Interconnection with accurate ratings
metadata.coverage: Western US - major transmission corridors including 500kV backbone, 345kV regional networks, 230kV sub-regional connections, and renewable energy integration lines
metadata.notes: Expanded with comprehensive regional networks connecting all major nodes. Includes major WECC paths (Path 15, Path 26, Path 66, COI, PDCI) and regional interconnections.
